WEBVTT

00:07.050 --> 00:08.399
[door slams]
[footsteps approach]

00:11.489 --> 00:14.318
- Uh, hello, everyone.

00:14.362 --> 00:16.712
I just wanted
to take this opportunity

00:16.755 --> 00:18.670
to say thank you
for even bringing me in.

00:18.714 --> 00:20.672
Um, this is
an amazing role, really.

00:20.716 --> 00:22.500
- I saw
your insurance commercial.

00:22.544 --> 00:23.588
- Oh, you saw that?

00:23.632 --> 00:25.373
I thought it came out
really well.

00:25.416 --> 00:29.377
My husband actually cried
the first time he saw it.

00:29.420 --> 00:31.205
[chuckles]

00:31.248 --> 00:32.771
- Uh, any questions for us?

00:32.815 --> 00:34.208
- Um, yeah, actually.

00:34.251 --> 00:38.429
Reading this, um,
what is my motivation?

00:38.473 --> 00:42.216
- Um, think of her
as a caretaker.

00:42.259 --> 00:43.521
- Okay.

00:43.565 --> 00:46.176
- Her authority comes from
a desire to protect.

00:46.220 --> 00:47.743
To do what's best
for those around her,

00:47.786 --> 00:49.788
she sets firm limits.

00:49.832 --> 00:51.312
- That's what I was thinking.

00:51.355 --> 00:54.097
Oh, and I also thought
that she would wear glasses.

00:54.141 --> 00:55.577
[chuckles]
Am I crazy?

00:55.620 --> 00:59.407
- No, that makes total sense.
- [laughs]

01:00.886 --> 01:03.715
[exhales, clears throat]

01:05.239 --> 01:07.284
"This is not a test.

01:07.328 --> 01:09.721
"This is your
emergency broadcast system

01:09.765 --> 01:12.550
"announcing the commencement
of the annual Purge

01:12.594 --> 01:15.379
"sanctioned
by the U.S. Government.

01:15.423 --> 01:17.599
"Weapons of class four
and lower

01:17.642 --> 01:20.732
"have been authorized
for use during the Purge.

01:20.776 --> 01:24.214
"All other weapons
are restricted.

01:24.258 --> 01:26.564
"Government officials
of ranking ten

01:26.608 --> 01:28.740
"have been granted immunity
from the Purge

01:28.784 --> 01:30.873
"and shall not be harmed.

01:30.916 --> 01:35.138
Commencing at the siren,
all crime except murder..."

01:35.182 --> 01:36.357
- [clears throat]

01:36.400 --> 01:37.836
- "Will be legal
for 12 consecutive hours."

01:37.880 --> 01:39.751
- Can we back up?

01:39.795 --> 01:43.233
The line as written
is "including murder."

01:43.277 --> 01:44.626
- Oh, right.

01:44.669 --> 01:46.758
"Including murder
will be legal," okay.

01:46.802 --> 01:50.458
[laughing]
Okay, but...

01:50.501 --> 01:52.590
[stammers]
I'm not telling them

01:52.634 --> 01:54.940
to go out
and kill people, right?

01:54.984 --> 01:57.378
- You're just stating
the rules.

01:57.421 --> 02:02.209
Um, try it again
from "commencing."

02:02.252 --> 02:03.775
Calm, reassuring.

02:03.819 --> 02:07.127
This is business as usual.

02:08.476 --> 02:11.827
[exhales sharply]
"Commencing at the siren,

02:11.870 --> 02:14.699
"all crime, including murder,

02:14.743 --> 02:17.441
"will be legal
for 12 continuous hours.

02:17.485 --> 02:21.271
"Police, fire,
and emergency medical services

02:21.315 --> 02:23.621
"will be unavailable
until tomorrow morning

02:23.665 --> 02:26.929
"at 7:00 a.m.,
when the Purge concludes.

02:26.972 --> 02:29.671
"Blessed be
our New Founding Fathers

02:29.714 --> 02:33.457
and America,
a nation reborn."

02:33.501 --> 02:36.199
[sinister music]

02:36.243 --> 02:39.942
May God be with you all.

02:39.985 --> 02:41.596
♪

02:41.639 --> 02:44.251
- Really nice work, Megan.
- [laughs]

02:44.294 --> 02:47.297
So what's this gonna be?
Like a movie or something?

02:47.341 --> 02:48.907
[dramatic music]

02:48.951 --> 02:51.910
[siren blaring]

02:51.954 --> 02:58.961
♪

03:03.879 --> 03:06.838
[peaceful music]

03:06.882 --> 03:09.841
[insects chirping]
[exotic birds calling]

03:09.885 --> 03:11.539
♪

03:11.582 --> 03:13.671
[alarm chimes]

03:13.715 --> 03:15.586
- It's time
to begin your shift.

03:15.630 --> 03:19.286
Please proceed to your
designated work station.

03:19.329 --> 03:22.463
[indistinct chatter]

03:22.506 --> 03:25.379
[phones ringing]

03:27.816 --> 03:32.255
[indistinct chatter]

03:35.911 --> 03:38.043
- Almost there, gang.

03:38.087 --> 03:39.871
Final Purge Night shift.

03:39.915 --> 03:44.267
Now, remember, the last
two hours can get a bit hectic.

03:44.311 --> 03:47.923
Not everything is legal,
so stay vigilant.

03:48.619 --> 03:50.882
- Possible derby
in district four.

03:50.926 --> 03:52.275
- Yeah, let's get the drone up.

03:52.319 --> 03:55.322
- Purgers spray-painted
16 of our cameras.

03:55.365 --> 03:57.889
[computer beeping]

03:57.933 --> 04:00.065
- Attempted breach.

04:00.109 --> 04:03.721
[foreboding music]

04:03.765 --> 04:06.811
[background chatter
continues]

04:06.855 --> 04:13.601
♪

04:23.611 --> 04:26.701
- There's two of them.
Let's keep an eye on them.

04:26.744 --> 04:33.751
♪

04:34.796 --> 04:36.319
- Watch your scans.

04:36.363 --> 04:39.496
[overlapping chatter]

04:39.540 --> 04:41.106
- Camera one is out again.

04:41.150 --> 04:43.587
- Action in sector 3.

04:43.631 --> 04:47.852
♪

04:50.507 --> 04:53.336
[computer chirps]

04:53.380 --> 04:54.685
[indistinct chatter]

04:54.729 --> 04:57.297
[computer hums, chirps]

04:59.429 --> 05:02.563
- That's odd.
- What's odd?

05:02.606 --> 05:04.216
[computer chirps]

05:04.260 --> 05:07.524
- Appears unarmed, but instead
of watching his surroundings,

05:07.568 --> 05:09.526
he keeps checking his bag.

05:09.570 --> 05:11.136
- What do you think
he's got in there?

05:11.180 --> 05:13.400
- I don't know,
let's take a look.

05:13.443 --> 05:15.967
[reversed audio warbles]

05:16.011 --> 05:17.969
[mouse clicks]

05:18.013 --> 05:21.016
[computer chirping, whirring]

05:22.844 --> 05:25.020
Hmm.

05:25.063 --> 05:27.762
- Bomb.
That's class five.

05:27.805 --> 05:31.026
- Suspected illegal weapon
on Lafayette.

05:31.069 --> 05:34.638
Yeah, I'm tagging it
right now.

05:34.682 --> 05:37.641
- Great work, Esme,
as always.

05:37.685 --> 05:39.469
♪

05:39.513 --> 05:41.166
- So what happens?

05:41.210 --> 05:42.951
- Remote detonate the device.

05:42.994 --> 05:45.388
If he survives tonight,
he won't much longer.

05:45.432 --> 05:46.824
It's a capital offense.

05:46.868 --> 05:49.566
- I don't get it.

05:49.610 --> 05:50.785
With so much leeway tonight,

05:50.828 --> 05:53.004
Why would he still
break the rules?

05:53.048 --> 05:57.008
- It doesn't really matter,
does it?

05:57.052 --> 05:59.707
As long as we catch him.

06:03.145 --> 06:05.060
[computer chirping]

06:05.103 --> 06:08.672
♪

06:08.716 --> 06:11.675
[all grunting, shouting]

06:11.719 --> 06:14.504
[suspenseful music]

06:14.548 --> 06:17.202
[grunting continues]

06:17.246 --> 06:19.204
- Take it easy,
take it easy.

06:19.248 --> 06:21.555
- [grunting]
- We're not gonna kill you.

06:21.598 --> 06:23.861
- But we are gonna
rob this bank,

06:23.905 --> 06:28.083
and Ryan here can't have you
getting in his way.

06:28.126 --> 06:30.738
- Sara, where are we at?
- Running the numbers!

06:30.781 --> 06:32.566
[device chirping]

06:32.609 --> 06:34.045
- Doug?
- [grunts]

06:34.089 --> 06:36.221
- How we looking outside?
- Clear on my end.

06:36.265 --> 06:39.529
- Copy that, let me know
if anything changes.

06:39.573 --> 06:41.531
[muffled explosion]
[car alarms wailing]

06:41.575 --> 06:44.012
[distant gunfire]

06:44.055 --> 06:46.014
- Pro tip: baby oil.

06:46.057 --> 06:48.712
Gets that tape right off.
[laughing]

06:48.756 --> 06:51.062
- [muffled grunting]

06:51.106 --> 06:53.456
- It's funny, Tommy.
Stay focused.

06:53.500 --> 06:55.763
- Always!

06:55.806 --> 06:58.548
Most of the time.
[laughing]

06:58.592 --> 06:59.680
[alarm blares]

06:59.723 --> 07:00.898
- Got it!
[clank]

07:00.942 --> 07:04.249
♪

07:04.293 --> 07:05.642
- Hey--

07:05.686 --> 07:07.252
- Ryan, I told you,
don't worry.

07:07.296 --> 07:08.993
I got this.

07:11.126 --> 07:12.127
- [sighs]

07:12.170 --> 07:16.087
♪

07:16.131 --> 07:17.741
- Ready?

07:17.785 --> 07:20.527
♪

07:20.570 --> 07:22.746
- Clear.

07:22.790 --> 07:25.270
♪

07:25.314 --> 07:28.491
Clear.

07:28.535 --> 07:30.754
♪

07:30.798 --> 07:32.930
[drill whirrs]

07:32.974 --> 07:36.194
♪

07:36.238 --> 07:37.500
Come on.

07:37.544 --> 07:43.201
♪

07:43.245 --> 07:46.988
[drill whirring]

07:47.031 --> 07:49.686
[computer chirping]

07:49.730 --> 07:51.209
- Oh, look at that.

07:51.253 --> 07:52.733
- They're practically
invisible.

07:52.776 --> 07:56.258
- Anti-surveillance headgear.
Illegal except on Purge.

07:58.260 --> 08:00.654
- Hey, what's the protocol

08:00.697 --> 08:02.786
for a ranked ten official
in distress?

08:02.830 --> 08:05.528
- Run facial recognition
to confirm level ten,

08:05.572 --> 08:08.183
tag it, then call upstairs.

08:10.794 --> 08:12.796
You okay?

08:12.840 --> 08:14.058
- I just got promoted

08:14.102 --> 08:16.017
from the district seven office
last week,

08:16.060 --> 08:19.281
so this is my first time
working Purge Night.

08:19.324 --> 08:22.806
This kind of crime is,
you know...

08:24.678 --> 08:26.636
I'm used to litterbugs
and rolling stops.

08:26.680 --> 08:27.985
- Yeah, first time's
the hardest--

08:28.029 --> 08:29.160
I'm not gonna lie, but...

08:29.204 --> 08:30.553
- [laughs]

08:30.597 --> 08:33.730
No, it's just a handful
of disturbing images

08:33.774 --> 08:36.298
burned into my brain
for life, but, hey.

08:36.341 --> 08:39.344
- I work every Purge, so--
- Jeez.

08:39.388 --> 08:43.566
- Yeah, reminds me
not to get complacent.

08:43.610 --> 08:44.872
Without the NFFA,

08:44.915 --> 08:49.572
this is what our world
could look like every day.

08:49.616 --> 08:50.921
- You really think so?

08:50.965 --> 08:52.096
- I've seen what people do

08:52.140 --> 08:53.620
when they think
no one's watching.

08:53.663 --> 08:55.273
- Damn, y'all, look!

08:55.317 --> 08:57.188
Bank robbers
are getting it done over here!

08:57.232 --> 09:01.192
- The IT department, however,
are a bunch of fucking tools.

09:12.987 --> 09:14.292
[ominous music]

09:14.336 --> 09:15.903
[distant gunfire]

09:15.946 --> 09:18.906
[dogs barking]

09:18.949 --> 09:25.869
♪

09:25.913 --> 09:28.916
[distant gunfire]

09:31.353 --> 09:34.356
[distant dogs barking]

09:40.318 --> 09:42.190
- What?

09:42.233 --> 09:44.714
- Just checking
if you were sleeping.

09:44.758 --> 09:48.892
- Hmm, it's kind of hard to
sleep with you staring at me.

09:48.936 --> 09:52.026
- Sorry.

09:52.069 --> 09:53.723
- It'll be over soon.

09:53.767 --> 09:56.900
- [sighs]
Not soon enough.

09:59.120 --> 10:01.078
This night just...

10:01.122 --> 10:04.299
kind of makes me start thinking
about what's really important.

10:04.342 --> 10:06.649
- Hold up.

10:08.869 --> 10:12.786
Are you trying to tell me
you want to have a baby?

10:12.829 --> 10:16.311
- Oh, a baby would probably
make this night even harder.

10:16.354 --> 10:18.356
- It does.

10:18.400 --> 10:21.969
That first year with Darren?

10:22.012 --> 10:25.668
Tonya, she practically had
a nervous breakdown.

10:25.712 --> 10:28.279
- And you?

10:28.323 --> 10:30.368
- I was at the window
with a shotgun.

10:30.412 --> 10:31.848
- No.
- Mm-hmm.

10:31.892 --> 10:34.677
- Seriously?
- Yep.

10:34.721 --> 10:36.940
- I just can't picture you
like that.

10:36.984 --> 10:39.290
I'm trying.

10:39.334 --> 10:43.991
- Mm, well, it was a different
zip code in those days.

10:44.034 --> 10:46.297
I like this one
a little bit more.

10:46.341 --> 10:48.343
- Mm.

10:48.386 --> 10:55.393
♪

11:02.270 --> 11:04.925
Mm.

11:04.968 --> 11:13.803
♪

11:13.847 --> 11:16.284
- [gags, retches]

11:16.327 --> 11:18.373
[vomits]

11:18.416 --> 11:20.157
[gagging]

11:20.201 --> 11:22.377
- Not again.
Really, Bill?

11:22.420 --> 11:23.857
- Here.

11:23.900 --> 11:25.946
Helps block the vomit smell
until they clean it up.

11:25.989 --> 11:27.425
- Thanks.

11:27.469 --> 11:29.166
- Let's get you
to the restroom.

11:29.210 --> 11:31.212
- Sorry.

11:31.255 --> 11:33.823
- You all right?
Come on.

11:33.867 --> 11:37.218
- I'm so sorry, guys.
- Every year.

11:42.049 --> 11:44.834
[distant gunfire]
[indistinct chatter]

11:44.878 --> 11:48.795
- Yo, Ben, good luck, man.
Do the thing!

11:48.838 --> 11:52.276
[car alarms wailing]

11:52.320 --> 11:54.017
- How far away
is this "suicide bridge"?

11:54.061 --> 11:56.933
- Uh, it's just a few blocks.

11:56.977 --> 11:59.762
[tense music]

11:59.806 --> 12:01.372
Yo.

12:01.416 --> 12:03.331
Ow.

12:03.374 --> 12:05.899
- We shouldn't be out here.

12:05.942 --> 12:08.771
- Dude, the scavenger hunt
is Delta tradition, all right?

12:08.815 --> 12:11.295
You'll be fine.

12:11.339 --> 12:14.298
[indistinct chatter]

12:14.342 --> 12:21.349
♪

12:27.529 --> 12:31.141
[all giggling, chattering]

12:31.185 --> 12:33.013
- [panting]

12:33.056 --> 12:34.144
That's some...

12:34.188 --> 12:35.972
[phone chimes]

12:36.016 --> 12:37.582
Jeff and Greg
are already on their way back.

12:37.626 --> 12:39.236
- I don't know, man,
this is insane.

12:39.280 --> 12:42.500
- Don't puss out on me.
We just need a photo.

12:42.544 --> 12:44.067
And, I mean, if it makes you
feel any better,

12:44.111 --> 12:47.288
they're already dead, right?

12:49.333 --> 12:53.424
Come on,
don't make me do this solo.

12:53.468 --> 12:56.297
- Okay, fine,
let's get it over with.

12:59.300 --> 13:03.478
[soft clicking]

13:07.134 --> 13:10.398
[click]
- One down.

13:10.441 --> 13:11.834
- Ignition stage
right on time.

13:11.878 --> 13:13.009
- Copy.

13:14.619 --> 13:17.405
- Hey, I got some
foot traffic here

13:17.448 --> 13:18.449
approaching
from the south alley.

13:18.493 --> 13:19.799
- You need me out there?

13:19.842 --> 13:22.453
- Hey, let's just slow
your roll, trigger man.

13:22.497 --> 13:24.978
Let's just see what we got.

13:25.021 --> 13:27.371
Looks like two hoods.

13:27.415 --> 13:34.204
♪

13:36.206 --> 13:38.295
Make that one.

13:38.339 --> 13:41.908
We're good.
Business as usual.

13:43.910 --> 13:46.477
[insects chirping]

13:46.521 --> 13:49.219
[object thuds distantly]

13:54.703 --> 13:57.488
- Michelle?

13:57.532 --> 13:59.969
[machine whirring]

14:00.013 --> 14:02.493
What the fuck?

14:02.537 --> 14:05.496
[foreboding music]

14:05.540 --> 14:08.021
♪

14:08.064 --> 14:09.936
[barricades clang]

14:09.979 --> 14:16.986
♪

14:21.295 --> 14:23.210
[clattering]

14:23.253 --> 14:25.560
[metal clinking]

14:25.603 --> 14:32.610
♪

14:44.231 --> 14:45.972
- Shh--quiet!

14:46.015 --> 14:49.192
I think someone
is in the house.

14:49.236 --> 14:51.891
♪

14:54.458 --> 14:57.548
- [breathing shakily]

15:03.511 --> 15:07.036
- [shakily]
Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

15:08.908 --> 15:11.867
[whispering]
Babe, let's go.

15:11.911 --> 15:14.478
Go, go, go.

15:18.569 --> 15:22.965
- [screaming]

15:23.009 --> 15:24.097
[Michelle screaming]

15:24.140 --> 15:26.969
[sinister music]

15:27.013 --> 15:29.624
Oh, God!
[whimpering]

15:29.667 --> 15:32.496
- I think I hit him.

15:32.540 --> 15:39.547
♪

15:42.028 --> 15:45.031
[dial clicking]

15:47.250 --> 15:49.209
[click]

15:49.252 --> 15:52.560
- Three down.
- Tommy, we're ready.

15:52.603 --> 15:54.823
- You guys don't move.

15:54.866 --> 15:57.913
♪

15:57.957 --> 16:00.220
[exhales sharply]
- How're the rent-a-cops?

16:00.263 --> 16:02.222
- Not willing to risk
their lives for minimum wage.

16:02.265 --> 16:05.921
[laughs] Tomorrow,
I'm giving my landlord

16:05.965 --> 16:07.618
two big middle fingers.

16:07.662 --> 16:10.795
- Oh, well, that would imply he
hadn't already kicked you out.

16:10.839 --> 16:14.060
- Again?
- It's the last time, I swear.

16:14.103 --> 16:15.670
Gonna buy me
a house tomorrow.

16:15.713 --> 16:17.889
- Got it.

16:17.933 --> 16:22.546
♪

16:22.590 --> 16:24.113
We're in.

16:26.681 --> 16:32.774
♪

16:32.817 --> 16:35.081
- [sighs]
There's your down payment.

16:35.124 --> 16:37.126
- Yeah!

16:40.782 --> 16:44.046
- [panting]

16:44.090 --> 16:46.744
[gun cocks]

16:46.788 --> 16:48.529
- [murmurs]
- Babe, come on.

16:50.574 --> 16:53.664
You gotta hide.
You gotta hide in here.

16:53.708 --> 16:55.797
- What are you doing?
- I've gotta get him out.

16:55.840 --> 16:57.929
- Of the house?
- Yes.

16:57.973 --> 17:01.020
I need you to reset the system
and close the barricades.

17:01.063 --> 17:02.499
- It's too dangerous.

17:04.153 --> 17:06.590
- I love you.

17:06.634 --> 17:08.810
I will be okay.

17:10.116 --> 17:11.900
- Be careful.

17:11.943 --> 17:17.645
♪

17:23.042 --> 17:26.001
- [panting]

17:26.045 --> 17:33.052
♪

17:36.751 --> 17:38.057
[door crashes, splinters]

17:50.286 --> 17:52.941
[hollers]

17:52.984 --> 17:59.991
♪

18:08.087 --> 18:10.001
[panel chirps]
[machine clangs]

18:10.045 --> 18:13.004
[machine whirring]

18:13.048 --> 18:17.139
♪

18:25.191 --> 18:28.063
- Yo, there should be
more Benjamins in here.

18:28.107 --> 18:29.717
- Not here.
We count later.

18:29.760 --> 18:31.066
- But if something's wrong,
we need to go

18:31.110 --> 18:33.068
hit the safe deposit boxes
like now.

18:33.112 --> 18:35.592
- Stick to the plan.
- We get one chance a year!

18:35.636 --> 18:36.985
- Yeah, and I don't want
to blow it.

18:37.028 --> 18:38.769
- But we have time!
- You don't know that.

18:38.813 --> 18:41.076
We got 66 minutes.

18:41.120 --> 18:44.210
Let's just get back safe
and then we count.

18:44.253 --> 18:47.604
♪

18:47.648 --> 18:49.824
[smacking door]

18:49.867 --> 18:53.175
- Hey, hey!

18:53.219 --> 18:55.177
I need your help!

18:55.221 --> 18:57.353
Somebody's trying to kill me.

18:57.397 --> 19:00.922
Hey, it's me.
Help me.

19:00.965 --> 19:03.925
From next door.
It's Marcus.

19:03.968 --> 19:06.971
[distant gunfire]

19:13.282 --> 19:15.284
[distant explosion]

19:28.471 --> 19:30.256
[dramatic music]

19:30.299 --> 19:33.259
[indistinct chatter]

19:33.302 --> 19:35.130
[gunfire]

19:35.174 --> 19:38.220
- What are you doing?

19:38.264 --> 19:41.136
- I was making sure
those guys are dead.

19:41.180 --> 19:48.012
♪

19:57.283 --> 20:00.068
- You see something?

20:00.111 --> 20:06.161
♪

20:08.642 --> 20:11.819
[dramatic music]

20:19.957 --> 20:22.482
[computer chirps]

20:22.525 --> 20:23.918
- Hey, Esme?

20:23.961 --> 20:27.313
Could you look at this
for me?

20:30.316 --> 20:32.666
- Mm, it's a
Kriss Vector rifle.

20:32.709 --> 20:34.494
It's weird as hell
but it's legal.

20:34.537 --> 20:35.886
It's class four.

20:35.930 --> 20:37.801
What sector are you working on?

20:37.845 --> 20:41.370
- Sector three,
but it's relatively calm.

20:42.676 --> 20:44.895
- Wait, go back.

20:46.636 --> 20:49.639
Is there a closer angle
on her?

20:53.948 --> 20:56.603
[computer beeping]

20:58.561 --> 21:00.302
[computer beeps]

21:00.346 --> 21:02.652
Oh, no.

21:02.696 --> 21:04.567
That's Drew Adams.

21:04.611 --> 21:08.310
- You know her?

21:08.354 --> 21:10.747
- She helped me out of
a really dark place.

21:10.791 --> 21:13.054
She's very special to me.

21:13.097 --> 21:14.925
I owe her a lot.

21:14.969 --> 21:17.537
- Oh, shit, Esme.

21:17.580 --> 21:21.062
- She hated this holiday.
She wouldn't be outside.

21:21.105 --> 21:23.282
- Maybe she didn't
have a choice.

21:23.325 --> 21:25.371
- Something's wrong.

21:25.414 --> 21:27.547
Come on.

21:27.590 --> 21:29.331
She needs to get inside.

21:29.375 --> 21:31.594
- Esme?

21:33.770 --> 21:36.425
Esme?

21:36.469 --> 21:38.645
- Yeah, no, uh, it's fine.

21:38.688 --> 21:40.299
She'll be fine, I'm sure.

21:40.342 --> 21:42.866
Send me a link
to that camera, would you?

21:49.830 --> 21:52.441
- It's supposed to be
right here.

21:55.792 --> 21:58.012
Holy shit.

22:00.710 --> 22:04.410
It really is a suicide bridge.

22:04.453 --> 22:07.543
[eerie music]

22:07.587 --> 22:14.550
♪

22:14.594 --> 22:17.771
- This is--this is awful.

22:24.473 --> 22:26.519
I feel bad
even taking her picture.

22:26.562 --> 22:29.652
- Yeah, but we need proof.

22:35.658 --> 22:37.791
That one kind of looks
like Kelen.

22:37.834 --> 22:39.706
- Why would you say that?

22:39.749 --> 22:41.925
- What?

22:41.969 --> 22:43.405
She clearly resembles
your girlfriend.

22:43.449 --> 22:44.928
- That's not funny, dude.

22:44.972 --> 22:48.628
- [stammers]
- I'm done with this night.

22:48.671 --> 22:51.718
- Dude, I was--I was just
making a joke.

22:52.762 --> 22:54.416
[shutter snaps]

22:54.460 --> 22:57.376
Would you wait?

23:05.862 --> 23:08.430
[approaching engine rumbling]

23:08.474 --> 23:10.824
[wheels squealing]

23:10.867 --> 23:14.567
- Car coming in hot!
Oh, you got something for me?

23:14.610 --> 23:18.701
[gunfire]

23:18.745 --> 23:22.488
Go get it!
How you like that, man?

23:22.531 --> 23:27.057
[gunfire continues]

23:30.800 --> 23:33.673
[indistinct shouting]

23:33.716 --> 23:36.458
[gunfire continues]

23:36.502 --> 23:38.504
[laughing]

23:38.547 --> 23:43.596
[gunfire continues]

23:43.639 --> 23:46.773
♪

23:46.816 --> 23:49.036
[engine clicking]

23:49.079 --> 23:51.865
[indistinct shouting]

23:51.908 --> 23:54.128
[gunfire continues]

23:54.171 --> 23:55.912
- Ooh--

23:55.956 --> 24:00.700
[indistinct shouting
continues]

24:00.743 --> 24:04.530
[intense music]

24:04.573 --> 24:11.580
♪

24:27.988 --> 24:30.947
- Get back.
- Freeze!

24:30.991 --> 24:33.123
- Shit, it's Jackals.
- Drop your weapons!

24:33.167 --> 24:35.648
Don't move--now!

24:35.691 --> 24:37.040
- That's enough,
that's enough!

24:37.084 --> 24:39.565
- Come on!

24:39.608 --> 24:41.480
Easy.

24:44.047 --> 24:46.615
- Ryan, you're too kind.

24:46.659 --> 24:50.576
Just wanna thank you for
cracking open that safe for us.

24:50.619 --> 24:53.274
Now, we weren't planning
on killing another crew,

24:53.317 --> 24:55.972
but if you don't give us
that cash...

24:58.497 --> 25:01.587
[suspenseful music]

25:01.630 --> 25:03.545
♪

25:03.589 --> 25:06.243
- Don't move.
- Easy.

25:06.287 --> 25:09.595
- Hand over the money
and you all live.

25:09.638 --> 25:11.248
- No problem.
Stay calm.

25:11.292 --> 25:13.990
- The cash, now!

25:14.034 --> 25:15.557
[dramatic music]

25:15.601 --> 25:18.038
- No, stop!
- Hey, hey, hey!

25:18.081 --> 25:20.083
[indistinct shouting]

25:20.127 --> 25:22.259
- Get up!

25:29.658 --> 25:31.660
- Who the hell are they?
- Jackals.

25:31.704 --> 25:34.445
Thieves who steal from
other thieves on Purge Night.

25:34.489 --> 25:36.578
- They look pretty
bad-ass, though.

25:36.622 --> 25:39.276
Hey, 50 bucks say
the robbers bite it.

25:39.320 --> 25:42.192
- I'll take that action.
- All right.

25:42.236 --> 25:45.195
[suspenseful music]

25:45.239 --> 25:53.073
♪

26:00.733 --> 26:03.344
- Hey, what do you say
we take a break?

26:03.387 --> 26:06.129
I could use a coffee.
- No, I can't.

26:06.173 --> 26:08.131
Not now.

26:08.175 --> 26:15.182
♪

26:24.365 --> 26:25.453
[exhales]

26:29.762 --> 26:32.591
- Come on, man,
we just gotta get back.

26:37.683 --> 26:42.470
- Help! Help!

26:42.513 --> 26:45.125
Please!
[sobbing]

26:45.168 --> 26:51.610
- Please, I need help.
Please.

26:51.653 --> 26:53.307
- It came from in here,
I think.

26:53.350 --> 26:56.049
- Don't be an idiot.

26:58.094 --> 27:01.097
- [gasps]
Oh, please, help me.

27:01.141 --> 27:02.838
Oh, please, please!

27:02.882 --> 27:06.276
Please untie this.
Just come--

27:06.320 --> 27:07.538
- Ooh--

27:07.582 --> 27:09.628
Aaah!

27:20.682 --> 27:23.337
Dude, help me, man!
- I'm trying, I can't do it!

27:23.380 --> 27:25.208
[overlapping shouting]

27:25.252 --> 27:26.732
- [sobbing]
- Hey!

27:26.775 --> 27:30.736
- Turner, come on, man!
You gotta get me out!

27:30.779 --> 27:34.565
- [sobbing]
No...no...

27:34.609 --> 27:37.090
Please don't--
[whimpers]

27:37.133 --> 27:38.657
No!
- Come on!

27:38.700 --> 27:40.354
- I'm sorry.
- Turner!

27:40.397 --> 27:42.791
Don't leave me!
- No--

27:42.835 --> 27:44.880
[woman sobbing]

27:44.924 --> 27:48.405
Do something!
Please--

27:48.449 --> 27:52.366
- Shh...
- [whimpering]

27:52.409 --> 27:55.238
Uhh--

27:55.282 --> 28:00.113
[wheezes, gasps]

28:08.643 --> 28:10.514
[clattering]

28:21.656 --> 28:23.876
- [whimpers]

28:23.919 --> 28:26.313
[cattle prod crackles]

28:32.406 --> 28:35.365
[cattle prod crackling]
- I'm not gonna hurt you.

28:35.409 --> 28:37.150
Maybe a little.

28:39.718 --> 28:41.676
- [shrieks]

28:47.638 --> 28:50.467
[suspenseful music]

28:50.511 --> 28:57.605
♪

29:02.349 --> 29:05.178
- Professor Adams,
where is the file?

29:05.221 --> 29:06.875
- Please, let me go.
Please.

29:06.919 --> 29:08.703
[static crackling]

29:08.747 --> 29:11.488
Please.
- File 64.

29:11.532 --> 29:13.273
- Please, please, please...
- No, please--

29:13.316 --> 29:14.491
[gunfire]
Aah!

29:14.535 --> 29:16.755
- No!

29:16.798 --> 29:18.974
[static crackling]

29:19.018 --> 29:21.847
[gunfire]

29:21.890 --> 29:24.850
[sinister music]

29:24.893 --> 29:31.900
♪

29:50.310 --> 29:52.660
- [whimpering]

29:52.703 --> 29:55.663
[suspenseful music]

29:55.706 --> 30:02.670
♪

30:30.872 --> 30:32.743
[horn honking]

30:32.787 --> 30:34.615
♪

30:34.658 --> 30:36.486
- Yeah, smoked him!

30:36.530 --> 30:38.662
- Attaboy!

30:41.970 --> 30:44.930
- You have five minutes.

30:44.973 --> 30:47.323
- Give up the money and we
all get out of here alive.

30:47.367 --> 30:49.978
- Don't do it.
We'll give them the money

30:50.022 --> 30:52.154
and they'll still shoot
our asses on the way out.

30:52.198 --> 30:54.069
- Yeah, I'm with Tommy.
- We got five minutes.

30:54.113 --> 30:55.505
- With four between us
and that door.

30:55.549 --> 30:57.943
- We're fucked.
- Yeah, but so are they.

30:57.986 --> 31:01.076
They run out the clock,
they're guilty, too.

31:01.120 --> 31:04.079
[suspenseful music]

31:04.123 --> 31:06.386
- Oh, shit.

31:06.429 --> 31:10.259
♪

31:10.303 --> 31:12.087
- I have a feeling
your guy here

31:12.131 --> 31:14.220
means a lot more to you
than mine did to me.

31:14.263 --> 31:16.091
- I'm sorry.

31:24.578 --> 31:27.450
[phones ringing]

31:34.588 --> 31:37.808
- Hey, Esme.

31:37.852 --> 31:39.593
Should you be watching this?

31:39.636 --> 31:42.857
- I can handle it.
- That's not what I meant.

31:42.901 --> 31:44.467
You would be
the first person to tell me

31:44.511 --> 31:47.427
this job wasn't
for personal use.

31:47.470 --> 31:49.298
- Something's off,
I can feel it.

31:49.342 --> 31:53.085
They were asking her
about file.

31:53.128 --> 31:55.565
Some kind of code, maybe?

31:55.609 --> 31:58.046
- Is it illegal?
Can you tag it?

32:00.309 --> 32:03.356
- [sighs]
No.

32:07.142 --> 32:08.317
You're right.

32:08.361 --> 32:10.319
[key clicks]
[computer chirps]

32:10.363 --> 32:13.148
It's not a case.

32:16.238 --> 32:19.850
You know what,
I could use that coffee now.

32:22.897 --> 32:25.204
Thanks.

32:25.247 --> 32:32.254
♪

32:39.348 --> 32:42.482
[computer chirping]

32:42.525 --> 32:49.532
♪

33:12.077 --> 33:15.036
- Yeah, shirt off.
[giggling]

33:15.080 --> 33:17.343
That's it.

33:17.386 --> 33:19.388
Pants too.

33:19.432 --> 33:21.956
- [whimpers]

33:22.000 --> 33:23.218
- It's okay.

33:23.262 --> 33:27.527
Just take it off.
Don't be afraid.

33:27.570 --> 33:29.050
Come on.

33:29.094 --> 33:33.141
Now, on your knees.
- [whines]

33:43.151 --> 33:45.327
It's beautiful.

33:47.068 --> 33:51.116
[murmuring]
It's okay.

33:51.159 --> 33:54.989
[intense music]

33:55.033 --> 33:57.731
♪

33:57.774 --> 34:00.386
Uhh...uhh...

34:00.429 --> 34:03.345
[gasping]

34:13.355 --> 34:15.270
Don't--please!

34:15.314 --> 34:19.492
I wasn't going to,
I swear!

34:19.535 --> 34:21.972
Aah--

34:31.591 --> 34:34.637
- 90 seconds.
- Now, get it now!

34:34.681 --> 34:37.249
- Okay, okay, don't shoot him.

34:37.292 --> 34:39.729
I'm gonna throw the money
out the door.

34:39.773 --> 34:41.296
- Hurry up!

34:48.086 --> 34:50.436
- Check it.

34:50.479 --> 34:52.612
Go!
- Get moving.

34:52.655 --> 34:54.092
- I'm on it.

34:56.355 --> 34:57.617
[whir, boom]

34:57.660 --> 34:59.619
[all holler]

34:59.662 --> 35:03.623
[high-pitched ringing]

35:03.666 --> 35:06.147
- I got him, I got him!
All right, go, go, go, go!

35:06.191 --> 35:08.802
- [gasping]

35:08.845 --> 35:10.760
- Oh, shit,
there goes our ride.

35:10.804 --> 35:13.415
- Where's the other bag?
- I had to leave it.

35:13.459 --> 35:15.200
- We need that cash!

35:15.243 --> 35:17.419
- Told you, man.
That's 50 bucks.

35:17.463 --> 35:18.725
- All right, people,

35:18.768 --> 35:20.509
less than 40 seconds
till end of Purge.

35:20.553 --> 35:22.642
Stand by for the sirens.

35:22.685 --> 35:26.733
And sirens in three,
two, one.

35:26.776 --> 35:30.432
[sirens blaring]

35:30.476 --> 35:31.607
- I'm going back.
- Sirens.

35:31.651 --> 35:34.741
- I can make it, I got this!
- Tommy!

35:34.784 --> 35:37.657
[sirens blaring]

35:39.746 --> 35:41.574
- [screams]

35:41.617 --> 35:43.619
[suspenseful music]

35:43.663 --> 35:46.622
[sirens blaring]

35:46.666 --> 35:53.629
♪

35:53.673 --> 35:56.371
[sirens continue]

35:56.415 --> 35:58.808
- Three seconds.
Two seconds.

36:03.248 --> 36:07.252
Told you I'd make it.
[laughs]

36:11.604 --> 36:14.128
Let's go.
- You can't come with us.

36:14.172 --> 36:17.697
- Come on, man.
- We have a code.

36:17.740 --> 36:19.351
- Damn, Tommy,
what were you thinking?

36:19.394 --> 36:21.266
- We need this!
- Stop it.

36:21.309 --> 36:22.441
They're watching.

36:25.095 --> 36:26.575
- Listen up.

36:26.619 --> 36:28.098
After the final siren,

36:28.142 --> 36:31.798
crimes may be prosecuted
to the full extent of the law.

36:31.841 --> 36:34.888
Let's get to it, people.

36:34.931 --> 36:37.064
I need your expertise
on something.

36:37.107 --> 36:39.719
- I'm busy.
- It's urgent.

36:39.762 --> 36:43.201
Bank robbery after the siren.

36:43.244 --> 36:44.463
- What's going on?

36:44.506 --> 36:46.160
- Apparently, you're too busy
taking bets

36:46.204 --> 36:48.945
to verify your own footage.

36:48.989 --> 36:52.079
[computer chirps]

36:52.122 --> 36:55.082
[suspenseful music]

36:55.125 --> 37:02.220
♪

37:02.263 --> 37:06.267
[siren blaring continuously]

37:19.411 --> 37:22.370
[siren slows, diminishes]

37:22.414 --> 37:25.634
♪

37:25.678 --> 37:28.811
[siren warbling]

37:28.855 --> 37:31.727
[reversed, clipped audio]

37:31.771 --> 37:34.730
[siren fading]

37:34.774 --> 37:38.299
♪

37:38.343 --> 37:40.170
- The old photo finish.

37:40.214 --> 37:43.826
- Oh, shit.

37:43.870 --> 37:46.786
His foot's on private property
after the siren,

37:46.829 --> 37:49.179
so that makes it
an off-Purge crime.

37:49.223 --> 37:51.312
- I made in time.
I know it.

37:51.356 --> 37:52.444
- I don't.

37:52.487 --> 37:55.011
Burn protocol,
meet at 1300.

37:55.055 --> 37:57.318
- I'm taking Doug
to the hospital.

37:57.362 --> 38:00.016
[grunts]

38:00.060 --> 38:02.149
- I'll see you after?

38:02.192 --> 38:05.805
- Really hope so.
- Armed robbery.

38:05.848 --> 38:07.676
[computer chirps]

38:07.720 --> 38:10.462
Call upstairs and initiate
liquidation protocol.

38:10.505 --> 38:13.465
[Myrkur's "Crown" playing]

38:13.508 --> 38:20.689
♪

38:23.736 --> 38:25.346
[barricades clattering]

38:25.390 --> 38:27.435
♪

38:27.479 --> 38:30.090
- [sighs]
Baby...

38:30.133 --> 38:32.745
[weeping]

38:32.788 --> 38:34.007
- It's okay.

38:34.050 --> 38:38.838
♪

38:38.881 --> 38:43.364
- ♪ Born at night

38:43.408 --> 38:46.149
♪

38:46.193 --> 38:50.328
♪ Many are called,
the few are chosen ♪

38:50.371 --> 38:52.417
♪

38:52.460 --> 38:57.160
♪ Open mouth

38:57.204 --> 39:00.076
♪

39:00.120 --> 39:03.993
♪ Swallow up
the lakes frozen ♪

39:04.037 --> 39:05.386
- It's over, he's dead.

39:05.430 --> 39:08.955
- Who was he?

39:08.998 --> 39:11.087
- Hey, I don't know.

39:11.131 --> 39:13.220
- Come.

39:13.263 --> 39:16.223
- I should get back out there.

39:16.266 --> 39:17.833
- Wait, wait, wait, wait--

39:17.877 --> 39:21.228
- Honey, I wanna know
who almost Purged me.

39:21.271 --> 39:23.317
♪

39:23.361 --> 39:25.754
- [sighs]

39:25.798 --> 39:27.974
Okay.

39:28.017 --> 39:31.238
♪

39:31.281 --> 39:34.894
♪ Sleep, little darling

39:34.937 --> 39:38.419
♪ Mother virgin

39:38.463 --> 39:41.988
♪ Darkness serpent

39:42.031 --> 39:45.470
♪ Come to feed me

39:45.513 --> 39:48.777
♪ Sleep, little darling

39:48.821 --> 39:52.390
♪ Bathed in moonlight

39:52.433 --> 39:55.393
♪ On her head

39:55.436 --> 39:59.222
♪ A crown of 12 stars

40:31.559 --> 40:34.301
[distant clattering]

40:34.344 --> 40:36.390
♪

40:36.434 --> 40:40.220
[car doors slamming]

40:40.263 --> 40:43.397
[distant sirens wailing]

40:43.441 --> 40:46.226
- Come on.

40:53.451 --> 40:55.496
- Where'd he go?

40:55.540 --> 40:58.412
He was--he was right here.

40:58.456 --> 41:04.244
[sirens increasing]

41:04.287 --> 41:06.376
- What?

41:13.035 --> 41:15.603
- What?
What is it?

41:19.564 --> 41:22.262
[phone beeps]

41:22.305 --> 41:24.220
- Oh, shit.

41:28.529 --> 41:30.531
He was following me.

41:30.575 --> 41:32.402
♪

41:32.446 --> 41:34.622
This wasn't random.

41:34.666 --> 41:38.017
♪

41:38.060 --> 41:40.410
He was targeting me.

41:40.454 --> 41:44.066
♪
